# Tool: AvailabilityTimeline
# Description: Generate a time-bucketed view of application availability showing
#   request counts, error counts, and availability percentage per time window.
#   Use for SLA reporting, availability analysis, or incident timeline reconstruction.
# Connector: Application Insights (ai-sre-demo)
# Parameters:
#   - timeRange (string): How far back to look (e.g. 1h, 6h, 24h)
#   - bucketSize (string): Time bucket size (e.g. 5m, 15m, 1h)

requests
| where timestamp > ago(##timeRange##)
| summarize
    total = count(),
    successful = countif(toint(resultCode) < 500),
    failed = countif(toint(resultCode) >= 500),
    avg_duration_ms = round(avg(duration), 1)
  by bin(timestamp, ##bucketSize##)
| extend availability_pct = round(todouble(successful) / todouble(total) * 100, 2)
| order by timestamp asc
